This paper is about designing a convolutional neural network (CNN) structure for predicting objects on different levels, such as image-level, region-level, and pixel-level. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the design of the network structure, which involves optimizing the network's performance, making it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of gradient information, which is a common topic in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the network in the COCO Detection 2018 challenge, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
